				<outline text="Does Your Member Of Congress Vote With Or Against Biden? https://t.co/C7L34tiS7x" type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 13:29:57 GMT" tweetId="1404430912302026752" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404430912302026752" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="1/2 Proof by induction. If a statement is true for 0, and if it being true for n implies it's true for n+1, then it's proven for all positive integers. When we let Dubya off for his sins, and when we didn't restructure the banking industry after the crash in 2008, we set the" type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 13:20:39 GMT" tweetId="1404428571410636803" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404428571410636803" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/2 stage for it to happen again, only worse. And Trump isn't done with us yet. He's the weird case of a former president who hasn't relinquished power. He hasn't learned how to use it yet, but he'll get more effective in his new role." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 13:20:43 GMT" tweetId="1404428587978133505" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404428587978133505" inReplyToId="1404428571410636803" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Joe Biden and Merrick Garland are acting like Donald Trump was a crazy dream. But the threat to American democracy will only get worse the longer we ignore it. https://t.co/qRKmMVAJca" type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:34:04 GMT" tweetId="1404416849434062857" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404416849434062857" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="We ignored Dubya and that led to Trump. 

I'm sure Biden and Garland know that.

They also want to avoid going to jail themselves when their terms are up." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:59:44 GMT" tweetId="1404423308582477831" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404423308582477831" inReplyToId="1404416849434062857" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="Journalism ought to start saying the things they never say that they know are true. I feel for them. But their jobs require them to do it. One of those things is in the parent of this tweet." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 13:00:42 GMT" tweetId="1404423551671808006" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404423551671808006" inReplyToId="1404423308582477831" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Something new for outliner devs in the #toolsforthought space.

https://t.co/Bpnb5Jt45d

It's what's behind all the ranting I've been doing about how import and export isn't enough in 2021." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:21:44 GMT" tweetId="1404413744327933956" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404413744327933956" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="A simple use-case to illustrate.

Imagine you're editing a blog post in your outliner. When you make a change, the blog publishing software (say WordPress or Substack) gets a notification that the outline was updated, along with the new version of the outline..." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:30:02 GMT" tweetId="1404415836895518721" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404415836895518721" inReplyToId="1404413744327933956" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="as a web sockets message. It then publishes the changed post without you doing anything more. 

Compare this to how it works without the connection. You make a change to the outline, copy the text to the clipbord, go into WordPress (or another blogging tool)..." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:30:03 GMT" tweetId="1404415837910487045" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404415837910487045" inReplyToId="1404415836895518721" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="open the post in their editor, and paste the changed version, and save. That's how things work now. All that work could obviously be done by software, no rocket science involved. All that's needed is a will on the part of developers to improve technology for users." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:30:03 GMT" tweetId="1404415838892011522" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404415838892011522" inReplyToId="1404415837910487045" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
								<outline text="That could be a competitive advantage, or something you do for your users because you have pride in your product, and you want to help them do what they do better." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 12:30:03 GMT" tweetId="1404415839869276167" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404415839869276167" inReplyToId="1404415838892011522" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Good morning everybody! How y'all doing?" type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 11:35:40 GMT" tweetId="1404402153821704193" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404402153821704193" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="I like Steely Dan, for sure, always have, but recently I've discovered that Katy Lied is by far my favorite album. I keep singing various Katy Lied songs as the background music of my life." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 11:40:40 GMT" tweetId="1404403413278994432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404403413278994432" inReplyToId="1404402153821704193" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="For example this is my song du jour.

https://t.co/9c3ShnOdjT

&quot;All I ask of you is make my wildest dreams come true.&quot;

Now that's a great idea." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 11:40:41 GMT" tweetId="1404403414679883777" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404403414679883777" inReplyToId="1404403413278994432" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="On another topic, I am fixated on the idea of integrating Twitter more and more into my blogging work. I see this as a positive influence on my public writing, and that of other #toolsforthought users." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 11:43:21 GMT" tweetId="1404404088301891587" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404404088301891587" inReplyToId="1404403414679883777" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
								<outline text="If we're going to have an open ecosystem, let's start with a tool that none of us own or control. One that has a nice API. And one that we all use (or so it seems)." type="tweet" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2021 11:43:22 GMT" tweetId="1404404089685938176" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1404404089685938176" inReplyToId="1404404088301891587" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
